<div type="description" n="monument">
<head>Description of Monument</head>
<p><rs type="material">White marble</rs> <rs type="objectType">sarcophagus</rs>, now broken, with five <rs type="decoration">standing figures</rs>, very worn (?or never completed) in relief, and a <rs type="decoration">robed figure</rs> at both corners. Copied from squeeze taken (apparently) before the stone was broken; reassembled in 1981.
For a fuller description see <bibl n="rrrs2006"> <author>Smith</author>, <title>Roman Portrait Statuary from Aphrodisias</title>,  <biblScope>Sarcophagus 1</biblScope></bibl>.</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="text">
<head>Description of Text</head>
<p><rs type="execution" key="scalpro">Inscribed</rs> above and between figures, and (l. 24) on lower moulding; the text must have begun on the lid. </p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="letters">
<head>Letters</head>
<p>Standard forms; ll.1-2, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.03</measure>; ll.3-23, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.02</measure>; l.24, <measure dim="height" type="length" unit="metre">0.025</measure>. Ligatures in ll. 6, 7, 8, 9, 15, 16, 19, 20, 24; <foreign lang="grc">ΠΟ</foreign> in ligature, l.2</p>
</div>
<div type="description" n="date">
<head>Date</head>
<p>
<date notBefore="0101" notAfter="0300" exact="none">Second to third centuries A.D.</date>
(<rs type="criteria">lettering</rs>)</p>
</div>
